Harrison Schmitt was the first member of [[NASA Astronaut Group 4|Group 4]] to be selected as a prime or backup crew member for an Apollo flight; from Group 4 he was the only astronaut to make it to the [[Moon]], with the [[Apollo 17|last Apollo mission]] at the end of 1972.

